User Requirement 017:
	STATEMENT Moderators (and sub-moderators) shall be able to invite users to their conference
		PRIORITY A/B
		
System Requirement 017.1:
	STATEMENT The conference-plugin shall provide a button to send invites to users
		PRIORITY A
		
System Requirement 017.2:
	STATEMENT A moderator shall be able to invite people from his contact list and shall be able to invite people via e-mail notification
		PRIORITY A
	
System Requirement 017.3:
	STATEMENT A Sub-moderator shall be able to invite people from his contact list only.
		PRIORITY B
		
System Requirement 017.4:
	STATEMENT A moderator shall be able to invite a complete group of contacts at once
		PRIORITY B
	
System Requirement 017.5:
	STATEMENT A invite via e-mail shall send an generated link to this conference only
		PRIORITY A
	
System Requirement 017.6:
	STATEMENT For every invited user shall be added a name-bar to the participant list
		PRIORITY A
		
System Requirement 017.7:
	STATEMENT The bar-size shall be the length of the users name plus 2 buttons for the moderator: 1. to remove a user 2. to set up is rights
		PRIORITY B
	
System Requirement 017.8:
	STATEMENT The participant-list shall be on left-hand side of every window, were every participant is listed
			  The participant-list shall have the same height as the window frame where the list is attached to
			  The participant-list shall have the same length as the longest user-bar
			  The list shall provide a function, to scroll trough the participants(if there is not enough space to show all participants)
		PRIORITY A
